{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:57:32.764Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"run_commands","toolCallId":"lnywrbqb","output":[{"query":"cat ./tasks.json || cat ./automation/tasks.json","result":"[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"00-preflight-project-context\",\n    \"title\": \"Preflight project context and guardrail audit\",\n    \"scope\": \"audit\",\n    \"target\": \"whole project\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform a preflight audit only. Do not edit files. Inspect package.json, app route tree, app/page.tsx, components/LandingPage.tsx, components/Header.tsx, components/Footer.tsx, components/sections, lib/site-map-data.ts, lib/public-page-content.ts, lib/landing-data.ts, lib/blueprint-data.ts, lib/frontend-placeholders.ts, components/Phase2PublicPages.tsx, components/Phase2InteractivePanels.tsx, and components/CommandCenter.tsx if they exist. Confirm the framework, routing model, styling stack, animation libraries, current page architecture, and whether framer-motion or motion/react is installed. Confirm whether any Aceternity UI components already exist; do not install anything. Check that there is no app/[...slug]/page.tsx and no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx. Search for PublicRoutePage imports and slug catch-all references. Check whether the landing page has all required homepage sections: Hero, Enterprise Quick Search, Garage Foundry Factory journey, What We Build, Interactive Experience, Global Presence, Client Success, Live Dashboard, Latest Research, Contact, Footer. Check whether all public pages are explicit App Router pages. Check whether the Blueprint scoring formula exists and whether the banking test case can return 87/100. Produce a gap list only. Do not edit files. Final response must include files inspected, missing items, route gaps, homepage gaps, design-system observations, animation-library availability, and recommended next task.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"01-safety-cleanup-no-slug-no-publicroutepage\",\n    \"title\": \"Remove forbidden slug route leftovers\",\n    \"scope\": \"routing-safety\",\n    \"target\": \"explicit public route architecture\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Implement only routing safety cleanup. Remove any forbidden catch-all slug route leftovers. There must be no app/[...slug]/page.tsx, no empty app/[...slug] directory, no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx, and no imports or references to PublicRoutePage. Do not redesign anything. Do not touch the landing page. Ensure all public pages remain explicit App Router pages. If an explicit page is missing, create a minimal explicit page file that uses the existing shared inner-page template, not slug logic. Run lint and build. Acceptance: no module-not-found for PublicRoutePage, no slug route files, no slug references, build passes, landing page unchanged.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"02-global-design-system-for-inner-pages\",\n    \"title\": \"Create premium inner-page design primitives\",\n    \"scope\": \"design-system\",\n    \"target\": \"public pages except landing\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or improve shared design primitives for all public inner pages except the landing page. Do not modify app/page.tsx, components/LandingPage.tsx, or existing landing sections. Inspect the landing page visual language and create inner-page-only components that follow its theme while allowing unique page designs. Build lightweight, maintainable components such as InnerPageShell, InnerPageHero, NarrativeSection, PremiumCTA, MotionReveal, BentoGrid, RelatedPagesGrid, ArchitectureDiagram, OperatingModelTimeline, EnterpriseFlowDiagram, AnimatedBackgroundGrid, PlatformProductPreview, IndustrySolutionMap, ResearchLibraryGrid, GlobalHubMap, SecurePortalPreview, and Carousel if useful. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Use Aceternity-inspired patterns such as bento grids, spotlight backgrounds, moving borders, sticky reveals, timelines, and card stacks by implementing lightweight local components with current Tailwind/CSS, not by installing heavy dependencies. Add SVG/CSS graphics and abstract visual panels. No external image URLs, no copyrighted images, no fake screenshots, no fake client logos. All components must be responsive, accessible, respect reduced motion, and scoped so they do not alter the landing page. Run lint/build. Final response must confirm landing page untouched.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"03-homepage-hero-preservation-and-metrics\",\n    \"title\": \"Verify approved hero and required metrics\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"landing hero\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Inspect the landing hero only. Preserve the approved hero UI exactly, especially the right-side video placement, hero layout, spacing, typography, video container, overlay, and responsive behavior. Do not redesign the hero. Verify the hero contains the required headline: Building the World's First AI-Native Enterprise Transformation Company. Verify the subheading: Combining Agentic AI, Knowledge Graphs, Industry Platforms, Talent Cloud, and Managed AI Operations into a single transformation ecosystem. Verify primary CTA: Generate My Enterprise AI Blueprint. Verify secondary CTA: Experience GFF AI Live. Add or preserve hero metrics in the least intrusive existing style: 500+ AI Use Cases, 20+ Industries, Global Delivery Model, Agent Factory, Knowledge Graph Factory, AI Academy. Do not create fake metrics. Do not replace the video with a dashboard or foundry visual. Run lint/build. Final response must confirm hero video placement untouched.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"04-homepage-enterprise-quick-search\",\n    \"title\": \"Restore or build Section 2 Enterprise Quick Search\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Enterprise Quick Search after hero\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add or restore Section 2 Enterprise Quick Search immediately after the approved hero. This section is mandatory. Preserve the approved hero and all existing landing styles. Build a local, frontend-only AI concierge style search that searches static local content across Industries, Capabilities, Platforms, Build With GFF tools, Resources, and Company pages. Include clickable example searches: Build AI for Banking, Create University AI Lab, Insurance AI, Mining AI, Retail AI, Build AI GCC. Results must appear instantly when typing or clicking examples. Each result must show title, category, short description, and route link. No API calls. No backend. No fake data. Design must be premium, clean, Apple-like, and consistent with the current landing theme. Use subtle Framer Motion or CSS transitions if available. Avoid box-inside-box clutter, excessive pills, badge soup, and neon overload. Mobile must be excellent. Acceptance: section appears after hero, search works locally, examples work, empty state is polished, links resolve, build passes.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"05-homepage-garage-foundry-factory-journey\",\n    \"title\": \"Complete Garage Foundry Factory journey\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Garage Foundry Factory journey\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the homepage transformation journey. It must include Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, Optimize, and Scale. Use the existing approved landing section if one already maps to this. Do not create duplicates. Do not redesign approved sections unnecessarily. Each step should have a concise description, outcome, and route link: Garage /platforms/garage, Foundry /platforms/foundry, Factory /platforms/factory, Operate /capabilities/operations or /platforms/control-center, Optimize /platforms/control-center, Scale /platforms/factory. UI should feel premium, like an enterprise operating model timeline, with subtle motion and responsive vertical mobile layout. Avoid visual clutter. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"06-homepage-what-we-build\",\n    \"title\": \"Complete What We Build section\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"What We Build capabilities section\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the homepage What We Build section. It must include these required cards: AI Strategy, AI Engineering, Agentic AI, AI Governance, AI Labs, AI Factory, AI Marketplace, AI Operations. Use existing approved card/grid design if present. Do not duplicate an existing capabilities section. Add links: AI Strategy /capabilities/strategy, AI Engineering /capabilities/engineering, Agentic AI /capabilities/agents, AI Governance /capabilities/governance, AI Labs /capabilities/labs, AI Factory /platforms/factory or /capabilities/operations, AI Marketplace /platforms/marketplace, AI Operations /capabilities/operations. Include secondary references where natural: Knowledge Graph, Data Platforms, Digital Twins, University Platforms, Managed Services. Design must be elegant, expensive, responsive, and not a generic card dump. Use subtle hover and reveal animations. No fake claims. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"07-homepage-interactive-experience\",\n    \"title\": \"Complete Interactive Experience section\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Interactive Experience tools section\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the Interactive Experience section on the homepage. It must include Talk to Agent, Blueprint Generator, AI Readiness, ROI Calculator, Marketplace, and Foundry Studio. Link to /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /platforms/marketplace or /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio or /platforms/foundry. If an existing BuildAIEnterpriseSection or similar approved section exists, update it minimally instead of replacing it. The design should feel like premium self-service enterprise tools, with tasteful cards or tabs, subtle motion, frontend-only preview behavior, no real API calls, and no fake outputs. Avoid nested boxes and excessive badges. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"08-homepage-global-presence\",\n    \"title\": \"Add Global Presence section\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Global Presence\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add or restore the Global Presence section on the homepage. Include Singapore as Global Headquarters, London UK as Client Innovation Centre or Client Center, India as AI Engineering Factory or Build Shop, and future regions Australia, Middle East, USA. Use an existing world map component if available. If not, create a lightweight SVG/CSS global hub visual or premium region grid. Do not add a heavy 3D globe dependency. Do not invent office addresses. Do not invent fake headcount unless already approved in content. Make the UI clean, cinematic, enterprise-grade, responsive, and aligned with landing theme. Add subtle motion or hover states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"09-homepage-client-success\",\n    \"title\": \"Add Client Success section\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Client Success\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add or restore the homepage Client Success section. Required elements: Case Studies, Video, Architecture, Business Outcomes. Use only anonymized representative patterns, never fake clients or fake logos. Representative patterns may include Global Banking Transformation, Healthcare Knowledge Operations, Manufacturing AI Factory, Retail Agent Operations. Label them as representative patterns. No fake numbers, no fake ROI, no fake customer names. Create a premium design with tabs, carousel, or narrative cards if appropriate. Include an architecture preview panel and outcome themes such as faster decision making, reduced manual effort, better knowledge access, improved compliance workflows, and improved employee experience. Mobile friendly. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"10-homepage-live-dashboard\",\n    \"title\": \"Add Live Dashboard preview section\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Live Dashboard\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add or restore the homepage Live Dashboard section. Required labels: Active Clients, Agents Running, AI Projects, Countries, Industries, Agent Health, Delivery, Spend, Adoption, Governance. Do not invent precise values. You may use only approved values such as 500+ AI Use Cases and 20+ Industries where appropriate. Other dashboard items must be label-only states such as Monitoring-ready, Connected in Control Center, Frontend preview, or Governance-ready. Design should feel like a premium enterprise AI operations control center, not a crypto dashboard. Use subtle animated status lines, charts without fake data, and clean dashboard panels. No backend, no real-time claims. Responsive and accessible. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"11-homepage-latest-research\",\n    \"title\": \"Add Latest Research section\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Latest Research\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add or restore the homepage Latest Research section. Include Articles, Videos, Podcasts, Whitepapers, plus links to Blog, Research, Case Studies, Architecture Library, Webinars, Events, Developer Docs, Downloads, Reports, Newsroom, Thought Leadership, and Patterns of Intelligence routes where they exist. Do not invent article titles with fake authors, fake dates, fake PDFs, or fake downloads. Use category cards, editorial visuals, research library previews, and coming-soon states. Design should feel like a premium research and intelligence library. Mobile friendly. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"12-blueprint-generator-compliance\",\n    \"title\": \"Verify and fix Blueprint Generator scoring\",\n    \"scope\": \"functionality\",\n    \"target\": \"Blueprint Generator\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Verify and fix the Blueprint Generator. It must be frontend-only and may appear on homepage and /build/blueprint. It must include title: Get Your Enterprise AI Blueprint in 60 Seconds. Required inputs: Industry, Company Size, Top Priorities with max 3 selection, AI Journey, Data Readiness, Leadership Commitment, Biggest Challenge, Email, OTP placeholder. Optional: Budget and Geography. It must not send real OTP or call backend. Formula: Blueprint Score = 0.20(AI Maturity)+0.25(Business Need)+0.20(Data Readiness)+0.20(Process Complexity)+0.15(Transformation Readiness). Scoring: No AI 10, Exploring AI 30, Running Pilots 60, Scaling AI 85, AI-Driven Enterprise or AI-Native 100. Business Need: Cost Reduction 20, Productivity 20, Customer Experience 15, Revenue Growth 15, Compliance 10, AI Transformation 20, Automate Processes 20, capped at 100. Data Readiness: Highly fragmented 20, Partially connected 50, Mostly integrated 75, Fully integrated 100. Process Complexity: <100 20, 100-1000 50, 1000-10000 80, 10000+ 100. Transformation Readiness: Not Discussed 20, Exploring 50, Budget Approved 80, Executive Mandate 100. Categories: 0-25 AI Beginner, 26-50 AI Explorer, 51-70 AI Adopter, 71-85 AI Transformer, 86-100 AI-Native Leader. Test example Banking, 15000 employees, Scaling AI, Productivity + Cost Reduction + Compliance, Mostly Integrated Data, Budget Approved must display 87/100. Required outputs: AI Readiness Score, Top 5 Recommended AI Opportunities, Recommended GFF AI Solution, Expected Business Impact, 90-Day Roadmap. Label impacts as expected/modelled, not guaranteed. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"13-nav-footer-and-sitemap-completion\",\n    \"title\": \"Complete navigation footer and sitemap links\",\n    \"scope\": \"navigation-footer\",\n    \"target\": \"Header Footer Sitemap\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Verify and complete the public navigation, footer, and sitemap route links. Do not redesign header or footer. Keep the current approved visual style. Header must include HOME, WHY GFF AI, CAPABILITIES, INDUSTRIES, PLATFORMS, BUILD WITH GFF, RESOURCES, COMPANY, CONTACT, CLIENT LOGIN. Footer must include Quick Links, Solutions, Industries, Platforms, Company, Legal, Newsletter where current layout supports it. Required legal/support links: Privacy, NDA, Terms, Investor Relations, Client Portal. All hrefs must resolve to explicit pages. Do not use slug routing. Do not create fake newsletter sending; frontend-only state only. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"14-command-center\",\n    \"title\": \"Command Center CmdK CtrlK\",\n    \"scope\": \"functionality\",\n    \"target\": \"Command Center\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Verify or implement a frontend-only Command Center. It should open with Cmd+K on Mac and Ctrl+K on Windows/Linux. Commands: Talk to Agent /build/talk, Generate Blueprint /build/blueprint, Estimate ROI /build/roi, Launch Sandbox /build/sandbox, Book Workshop /contact. It must be keyboard accessible, have focus handling, work on desktop, and have a safe mobile trigger if needed. Use existing header or global layout mounting without redesigning the header or landing page. No API calls. Use premium modal/command UI inspired by modern command palettes and Aceternity-style effects if lightweight. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"15-frontend-only-placeholder-safety\",\n    \"title\": \"Ensure frontend-only placeholders\",\n    \"scope\": \"frontend-safety\",\n    \"target\": \"forms and interactive tools\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Audit and fix all forms and interactive tools to be frontend-only placeholders. Check Contact, Newsletter, Portal login, Control Center, Talk to Agent, Blueprint, Assessment, ROI, Sandbox, Proposal Builder, Marketplace, Foundry Studio. No real API calls, no auth, no AWS, no OTP sending, no real email sending, no database calls, no export file generation, no env dependency. If an existing legacy API route exists, do not use it from the public frontend. Placeholder copy must clearly say backend/FastAPI integration will come later only where appropriate. Run grep/search for fetch, axios, app/api calls, localhost, NEXT_PUBLIC_API, AWS, Cognito, SES, S3. Fix violations only. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"16-why-gff-ai-design-family\",\n    \"title\": \"Design Why GFF AI page family\",\n    \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n    \"target\": \"Why GFF AI explicit pages\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /why-gff-ai and all Why GFF AI subpages into a premium executive narrative design family. Do not touch the landing page. Pages: /why-gff-ai, /why-gff-ai/mission, /why-gff-ai/vision, /why-gff-ai/garage-foundry-factory, /why-gff-ai/operating-model, /why-gff-ai/leadership, /why-gff-ai/global-model, /why-gff-ai/technology-philosophy, /why-gff-ai/differentiator. Design mood: strategic, editorial, boardroom-level, global, premium. Use unique page-specific hero visuals, narrative sections, operating model diagrams, timeline/storytelling blocks, global hub visuals, research/IP panels, differentiator grids, carousels or tabs where useful. Use Framer Motion if available, lightweight Aceternity-inspired bento/timeline/spotlight patterns, CSS/SVG graphics, and responsive layouts. Content must include GFF AI PTE LTD., UEN 202621347N where appropriate, Architects of the Agent Economy, Dr. Ashish Chandra only where approved, Singapore Global HQ, London Client Innovation Centre, India AI Engineering Factory, Garage Innovation Layer, Foundry Co-Creation Layer, Factory Industrialisation Layer, GFF AI Research Division, proprietary indices, Agentic GDP Index, Digital Labour Penetration Score, AI Board Readiness Index, GFF AI Reference Architecture. Do not invent other leaders, addresses, clients, or fake metrics. Leadership page must use approved Dr. Ashish Chandra and polished placeholders for other profiles if needed. Every page must have one H1, strong narrative, CTA, related links, mobile excellence. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"17-capabilities-design-family\",\n    \"title\": \"Design Capabilities page family\",\n    \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n    \"target\": \"Capabilities explicit pages\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /capabilities and all capability subpages into a premium technical architecture design family. Do not touch landing page. Pages: /capabilities, /capabilities/strategy, /capabilities/engineering, /capabilities/agents, /capabilities/governance, /capabilities/data, /capabilities/labs, /capabilities/operations, /capabilities/twins, /capabilities/universities, /capabilities/knowledge-graph, /capabilities/managed-services. Design mood: technical, architectural, systems-driven, precise, credible, expensive. Build a unique capabilities landing page with capability command grid, enterprise AI stack, Agent Factory and Knowledge Graph Factory visual, Garage-to-Factory mapping, related platforms, and CTA. Subpages must share a coherent family template but feel tailored through unique hero visuals, use-case grids, architecture diagrams, delivery model panels, business outcome sections, tabs or carousels where helpful, and related platforms/industries. Use SVG/CSS architecture visuals with layers such as Experience Layer, Agentic AI Layer, Knowledge Graph Layer, Data and Integration Layer, Governance Layer, Managed AI Operations Layer. Use Framer Motion and Aceternity-inspired bento, spotlight, moving-border, sticky reveal, or tab patterns if lightweight. Do not make legal/compliance/ROI guarantees. No fake clients or dashboards. Mobile excellent. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"18-industries-hub-and-batch1\",\n    \"title\": \"Design Industries hub plus Financial Services Banking Insurance\",\n    \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n    \"target\": \"Industries hub batch 1\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /industries, /industries/financial-services, /industries/banking, and /industries/insurance. Do not touch landing page. Design mood: industry-specific, outcome-driven, executive, practical, premium. /industries should feel like a high-end industry solution map with industry selector, carousel or tabbed grid, common challenge patterns, reference solution architecture, common enterprise agents, and CTA to Build AI for Your Industry. Each industry subpage must include: industry hero, challenge landscape, reference solution, architecture visual, AI agent map, business outcome levers, demo preview, ROI/value levers without fake percentages, Talk to Agent CTA, related platforms and capabilities. Financial Services challenges: legacy systems, compliance pressure, fragmented data, manual documentation, risk visibility. Banking challenges: customer service scale, compliance review, knowledge fragmentation, manual back-office processes, product/policy search. Insurance challenges: claims operations, policy search, risk assessment, document-heavy workflows, customer response time. Use agents such as Compliance Assistant, Customer Intelligence Agent, Risk Review Agent, Knowledge Search Agent, Executive Dashboard Agent, Banking Knowledge Agent, Relationship Manager Copilot, Contract Intelligence Agent, Claims Triage Agent, Policy Intelligence Agent, Underwriting Copilot. No fake clients, fake logos, fake ROI, or guarantees. Use clean graphics, carousels/tabs, Framer Motion if available, and responsive mobile layouts. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"19-industries-batch2-health-education\",\n    \"title\": \"Design Healthcare Life Sciences Education pages\",\n    \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n    \"target\": \"Industries batch 2\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /industries/healthcare, /industries/life-sciences, and /industries/education using the same premium industry family design but tailored visuals and content. Do not touch landing page. Healthcare challenges: operational complexity, patient communication workflows, staff knowledge access, administrative burden, compliance-sensitive processes. Life Sciences challenges: research documentation, regulatory workflows, knowledge management, trial operations support, cross-functional collaboration. Education challenges: student support, faculty enablement, knowledge access, university operations, AI labs and learning platforms. Suggested agents: Care Operations Copilot, Knowledge Search Agent, Document Intelligence Agent, Scheduling Assistant, Executive Dashboard Agent, Research Knowledge Agent, Re\n[... output truncated: 146087 chars total. Refine the command (grep, head, tail) to view the elided middle ...]\nperations APIs\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP AI Operations APIs under /api/v1/ai-operations. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. This is only for portal/admin AI operations records, not live GFF AI tool execution. Endpoints: GET list, GET by id, POST create, PATCH update, DELETE or archive. Admin roles can manage all. Client roles can read only records for their client_id. Include filters: client_id, project_id, status, health, agent_type, governance_status, owner. No real agent runtime, no live monitoring, no external AI calls. Use representative database records only.  Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"137-phase5-api-documents-metadata-crud\",\n    \"title\": \"Build Documents metadata CRUD APIs\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-portal-admin-api\",\n    \"target\": \"documents metadata APIs\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP Documents APIs under /api/v1/documents. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. This phase manages metadata only. No real upload, no file storage, no S3, no download. Endpoints: GET list, GET by id, POST create metadata, PATCH update metadata, DELETE or archive metadata. Admin roles can manage all. Client roles can list/view documents for their client_id where visibility allows. Include fields like title, document_type, status, version, owner, project_id, visibility. Include filters: client_id, project_id, document_type, status, visibility, search. If frontend has upload/download buttons, they must remain disabled or future integration. Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"138-phase5-api-billing-invoices-crud\",\n    \"title\": \"Build Billing and invoice metadata APIs\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-portal-admin-api\",\n    \"target\": \"billing APIs\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP invoice/billing APIs under /api/v1/invoices or /api/v1/billing. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. No payment provider, no payment processing, no PDF generation, no tax engine, no external finance system. Endpoints: GET list, GET by id, POST create invoice metadata, PATCH update invoice metadata, DELETE or archive. Admin/finance roles can manage. Client roles can read only their client_id invoices. Include filters: client_id, project_id, status, month/date range if simple, search.  Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"139-phase5-api-support-tickets-crud\",\n    \"title\": \"Build Support ticket CRUD APIs\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-portal-admin-api\",\n    \"target\": \"support APIs\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP support ticket APIs under /api/v1/support or /api/v1/tickets. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET list, GET by id, POST create, PATCH update, PATCH status, PATCH assign, add comment if simple. Admin/support roles can manage all tickets. Client roles can create and view their own client tickets. No email sending, no file attachments, no uploads. Include fields: title, description, category, priority, status, client_id, project_id nullable, assigned_to, created_by. Include filters: status, priority, category, client_id, project_id, assigned_to, search. Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"140-phase5-api-governance-crud\",\n    \"title\": \"Build Governance item CRUD APIs\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-portal-admin-api\",\n    \"target\": \"governance APIs\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP governance APIs under /api/v1/governance. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET list, GET by id, POST create, PATCH update, PATCH status, DELETE or archive. Admin roles can manage all. Client roles can read their client_id governance items and optionally  if the Phase 4 UI already supports local preview. No legal/compliance guarantees. Include filters: client_id, project_id, severity, status, owner, due date, search.  Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"143-phase5-api-dashboard-summary\",\n    \"title\": \"Build dashboard summary APIs\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-portal-admin-api\",\n    \"target\": \"dashboard APIs\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP dashboard summary APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET /api/v1/dashboard/client for client portal summary and GET /api/v1/dashboard/admin for admin summary. Client dashboard should return counts and recent records for that user's client_id: active projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, open support tickets, governance items. Admin dashboard should return global counts and recent records across clients: clients, projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, governance Values must come from local database records, not hardcoded frontend mock data. Keep queries simple. Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"144-phase5-api-analytics-summary\",\n    \"title\": \"Build analytics summary APIs\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-portal-admin-api\",\n    \"target\": \"analytics APIs\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP analytics APIs under /api/v1/analytics. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET /api/v1/analytics/client and GET /api/v1/analytics/admin. Use database aggregation from projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support tickets, governance items. Keep it simple: counts by status, counts by phase, support by priority, invoice by status, AI operations by health, governance by severity. No fake live analytics. No external analytics provider. Client roles see only their client_id data. Admin roles see all. Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"145-phase5-backend-error-handling-and-pagination\",\n    \"title\": \"Add backend error handling pagination and response consistency\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-backend-quality\",\n    \"target\": \"API consistency\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Improve backend API consistency. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Add simple pagination parameters where useful: limit and offset with safe defaults. Add consistent 404 handling, unauthorized, forbidden, validation error behavior, and simple response shapes. Do not overengineer. Ensure list endpoints do not return hashed passwords or sensitive fields. Ensure client RBAC filters are enforced server-side. Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"146-phase5-backend-smoke-tests\",\n    \"title\": \"Add backend smoke tests or verification script\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-backend-quality\",\n    \"target\": \"backend verification\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add lightweight backend smoke tests or a verification script. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. If pytest is available or easy to add safely, add tests for health, login, auth/me, RBAC blocked admin route for client user, client dashboard data scoping, projects list, support ticket create, and . If adding pytest is too much, create a backend smoke script using FastAPI TestClient if available. Keep it small. Document how to run. Run backend checks.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"147-phase5-frontend-api-client\",\n    \"title\": \"Create frontend API client for portal and admin only\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"frontend API client\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create a frontend API client for portal/admin backend integration. Do not touch landing page. Do not connect GFF AI tools to backend. The API client should support base URL from NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL defaulting to local backend, bearer token handling, JSON request helpers, typed functions, error handling, and logout on unauthorized if safe. Add modules for auth, dashboard, clients, users, projects, aiOperations, documents, invoices, support, governance, analytics. Keep it small and readable. Do not use axios unless already used; fetch is fine. Ensure code is client-safe and does not break SSR. Run frontend lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"148-phase5-frontend-auth-integration\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect login UI to backend auth\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"login backend integration\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /login and /portal/login to the MVP backend auth endpoints. Do not touch landing page. Do not modify GFF AI tools. Replace or wrap the Phase 4 local preview login so users can login against /api/v1/auth/login when backend is configured. Store access token in localStorage for MVP dev only with clear TODO for production httpOnly cookie/session hardening. Call /api/v1/auth/me to load current user. Preserve role preview fallback only if backend is unavailable, clearly labelled dev fallback. Sign out should clear token/session and route to /portal/login. Do not add OAuth, OTP, email, SSO, or production cookies. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"149-phase5-frontend-route-guard-backend-auth\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect route guards to backend auth and RBAC\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"route guards\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Update private route guards to use backend auth state from /auth/me and stored MVP token. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Client roles should access /portal routes. Admin roles should access /admin routes. Unauthorized users should go to /portal/login or show sign-in required. Forbidden role access should show a polished Access Restricted page. Keep Phase 4 preview mode only as fallback if explicitly needed. Ensure hydration safety and no infinite redirect loops. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"150-phase5-frontend-client-dashboard-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Client Dashboard to backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/dashboard\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/dashboard to the MVP backend dashboard API. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace static mock dashboard data with data fetched from /api/v1/dashboard/client when authenticated. Keep graceful loading, error, empty, and offline/dev fallback states. Use the existing premium Phase 4 UI and preserve its design. Do not redesign. Ensure data is client-scoped by backend. Widgets: projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, analytics, governance. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"151-phase5-frontend-client-projects-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Client Projects to backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/projects\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/projects and project detail/drawer to backend /api/v1/projects. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Client users should fetch only their own projects as enforced by backend. Replace static mock data with API data while preserving Phase 4 UI. Implement loading, empty, error, retry, search/filter using API params or local filtering if simpler. Client view should remain mostly read-only for MVP. Admin project management is handled separately. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"152-phase5-frontend-client-ai-operations-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Client AI Operations to backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/ai-operations\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/ai-operations and AI operation detail/drawer to backend /api/v1/ai-operations. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. This is only portal operational records, not live AI tool execution. Preserve the Phase 4 premium UI. Add loading, empty, error, and retry states. Client users should see only their client_id records. No real-time monitoring, no websockets, no external AI calls. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"153-phase5-frontend-client-documents-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Client Documents to backend metadata API\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/documents\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/documents and document detail/drawer to backend /api/v1/documents. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. This phase is metadata-only. No upload, no download, no file storage. Replace static mock metadata with backend records. Keep upload/download controls disabled or future integration notes. Add loading, empty, error, retry states, search/filter if simple, and preserve UI. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"154-phase5-frontend-client-billing-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Client Billing to backend invoice API\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/billing\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/billing and invoice list/detail to backend invoice API. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. This phase is invoice metadata only. No payment, no PDF, no download. Replace static invoices with backend data. Keep disabled/future payment/download actions. Add loading, empty, error, retry states. Preserve Phase 4 premium finance UI. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"155-phase5-frontend-client-support-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Client Support to backend tickets API\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/support\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/support and ticket detail/drawer to backend support ticket APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Client users must be able to list their tickets and create a new ticket through POST. If comments endpoint exists, allow frontend-only or backend comment based on API availability. No email sending, no file attachments. Preserve Phase 4 premium support UI. Add loading, empty, error, success, retry, and validation states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"156-phase5-frontend-client-analytics-governance-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Client Analytics and Governance to backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/analytics and /portal/governance\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/analytics to /api/v1/analytics/client and /portal/governance to /api/v1/governance. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace static data with backend summaries and governance records. Governance read actions may be backend-connected if endpoint exists, otherwise keep read-only. Preserve Phase 4 visual design, charts, filters, and mobile behavior. Add loading, empty, error, and retry states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"158-phase5-frontend-admin-dashboard-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Dashboard to backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/dashboard\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin and /admin/dashboard to backend /api/v1/dashboard/admin. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace static admin dashboard data with backend data. Preserve Phase 4 premium admin UI. Add loading, empty, error, retry states. Admin dashboard should show clients, projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, governance,  based on database records. No fake live data. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"159-phase5-frontend-admin-clients-users-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Clients and Users to backend CRUD\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/clients and /admin/users\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/clients and /admin/users to backend CRUD APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Admin clients page should list, search/filter, create, edit, archive if API supports it. Admin users page should list, search/filter, create, edit role/status, deactivate if API supports it. Use modals or drawers that preserve existing UI. Add loading, empty, error, success, validation, and retry states. Enforce frontend role visibility based on backend current user, but backend remains source of truth. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"160-phase5-frontend-admin-projects-aiops-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Projects and AI Operations to backend CRUD\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/projects and /admin/ai-operations\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/projects and /admin/ai-operations to backend CRUD APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Admin projects page should list, filter, create, edit, archive projects if API supports it. Admin AI operations page should list, filter, create, edit, assign owner, update status/health/governance if API supports it. Preserve Phase 4 UI with drawers/modals. No live agent runtime. Add loading, empty, error, success states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"161-phase5-frontend-admin-documents-billing-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Documents and Billing to backend CRUD\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/documents and /admin/billing\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/documents to backend document metadata CRUD and /admin/billing to invoice metadata CRUD. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Documents are metadata-only, no upload/download/storage. Billing is invoice metadata-only, no payment/PDF. Admin should list, create metadata, edit metadata, archive if API supports it. Preserve Phase 4 UI and disabled future integration controls. Add loading, empty, error, success, validation states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"162-phase5-frontend-admin-support-governance-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Support and Governance to backend CRUD\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/support and /admin/governance\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/support to backend support ticket APIs and /admin/governance to backend governance APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Admin support should list, filter, assign, update status, and optionally add local/backend comment depending on API. Admin governance should list, filter, create, update status, assign reviewer if API supports it. Preserve Phase 4 premium UI. No email, no attachments, no compliance guarantees. Add loading, empty, error, success, retry states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"165-phase5-remove-old-local-preview-data-dependency\",\n    \"title\": \"Reduce dependency on Phase 4 local mock data in portal admin\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-cleanup\",\n    \"target\": \"mock data cleanup\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Reduce reliance on Phase 4 local mock data for portal/admin pages now connected to backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Keep local mock data only as fallback or for non-backend preview sections. Portal/admin dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance,clients, and users should prefer backend API data. Do not delete shared mock data if still used safely by non-integrated components, but clearly separate backend-connected data from fallback data. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"166-phase5-dev-environment-docs\",\n    \"title\": \"Document local dev environment for MVP backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-docs\",\n    \"target\": \"local dev documentation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or update docs/PHASE_5_MVP_BACKEND.md. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Document how to install backend dependencies, create .env from .env.example, initialize SQLite, run seed, start backend, start frontend, configure NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL, login with seeded dev users, and test portal/admin flows. Document that this phase is local/dev MVP only and does not include AWS, storage, payments, email, OTP, OAuth, SSO, production auth hardening, or backend for GFF AI tools. Include troubleshooting for CORS, missing DB, invalid token, and seed rerun. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"167-phase5-security-limitations-docs\",\n    \"title\": \"Document MVP security limitations and Phase 6 hardening\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-docs\",\n    \"target\": \"security documentation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or update docs/PHASE_5_SECURITY_LIMITATIONS.md. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Document MVP security limitations honestly: JWT in localStorage or dev storage, SQLite local DB, local seed users, no production password reset, no MFA, no refresh token hardening, no httpOnly secure cookie implementation unless already done, no rate limiting, no audit-grade logs, no production RBAC review, no file scanning, no payment compliance. Document required Phase 6 hardening steps: production database, httpOnly secure cookies or hardened session strategy, refresh token rotation, password reset, MFA/SSO optional, rate limiting, audit logs, secrets management, deployment config, CORS hardening. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"168-phase5-backend-frontend-smoke-qa\",\n    \"title\": \"Run backend and frontend smoke QA\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-quality\",\n    \"target\": \"local full stack smoke QA\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform a local full-stack smoke QA for Phase 5. Do not add features unless fixing small clear issues. Verify backend can start, health endpoint works, database initializes, seed script works, dev users can login, /auth/me returns current user, client user cannot access admin APIs, admin user can access admin APIs, client portal dashboard fetches data, admin dashboard fetches data, support ticket create works, documents are metadata-only, invoices are metadata-only. Verify frontend builds. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Run available backend checks/tests and frontend lint/build. Fix only issues found during smoke QA.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"169-phase5-no-gff-tools-backend-regression-audit\",\n    \"title\": \"Audit that GFF AI tools remain frontend-only\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-safety\",\n    \"target\": \"GFF AI tools backend exclusion\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Audit that Phase 3 GFF AI tools remain frontend-only and were not accidentally connected to backend. Do not touch landing page. Check /build/blueprint, /build/roi, /build/proposal, /build/assessment, /build/sandbox, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio, /build/talk. These should not call the new backend APIs in Phase 5. They may still use local state, localStorage, deterministic calculations, and frontend preview behavior. If accidental backend integration exists in these tools, remove it and restore frontend-only behavior. Do not change their UI unless required to remove backend calls. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"170-phase5-final-mvp-backend-qa\",\n    \"title\": \"Final Phase 5 MVP backend QA\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-final-qa\",\n    \"target\": \"MVP backend auth RBAC portal admin integration\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform final QA for Phase 5. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify local/dev backend exists and runs. Verify SQLite database setup. Verify seed data and dev users. Verify JWT login, auth/me, logout, RBAC, client data scoping, admin access. Verify CRUD APIs for clients, users, projects, AI operations, documents metadata, invoices metadata, support tickets, governance, dashboard summaries, analytics summaries. Verify frontend login connects to backend. Verify client portal pages use backend data: Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Activity, Settings. Verify admin pages use backend data: Dashboard, Clients, Users, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings. Verify no AWS, storage, payment, email, OTP, OAuth, SSO, production auth, or backend for GFF AI tools was added. Verify landing page unchanged. Run backend tests/checks if available, backend startup/import checks, npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, local dev login credentials from seed docs, and TODOs for Phase 6 production hardening.\"\n  }\n]\n\n[stderr]\ncat: ./tasks.json: No such file or directory\n","success":true}],"durationMs":17}}
